50|$|The {{final resting}} place <b>of</b> <b>Habakkuk</b> has been claimed at {{multiple}} locations. The fifth-century Christian historian Sozomen claimed that the relics <b>of</b> <b>Habakkuk</b> were found at Cela, when God revealed their location to Zebennus, bishop of Eleutheropolis, in a dream. Currently, one location in Israel and one in Iran lay claim to being the burial site of the prophet.|$|R
